text: Prins van Oranje or Prinses van Oranje may refer to: *Prince of Orange, a title given to the male heir apparent of the Dutch throne *Princess of Orange, the title given to the female heir apparent of the throne Prins van Oranje or De Prins van Oranje may also refer to: ==People== *Willem, Prins van Oranje (1815-40) *Willem, Prins van Oranje (1840-49) *Willem, Prins van Oranje (1849-79) *Alexander, Prins van Oranje (1879-84) *Willem-Alexander, Prins van Oranje (1980-2013) *Catharina-Amalia, Prinses van Oranje (since 2013) ==Military== *, a class of two minelayers in service with the Royal Netherlands Navy from 1932-43 *Regiment Huzaren Prins van Oranje, an armoured regiment of the Royal Netherlands Army. ==Windmills== *De Prins Van Oranje, Bredevoort, a windmill in Gelderland *De Prins Van Oranje, Buren, a windmill in Gelderland
